verbose_text: Notably, ablation of GH-R attenuated the caspase-1 cleavage and IL-1beta activation when NLRP3 inflammasome was primed by substituting LPS with a different TLR4 agonist lipid A (LA) or TLR2 ligands, peptidoglycan (PGN) and lipoteichoic acid (LTA), and signal-2-dependent inflammasome assembly was induced by ATP and urate (XREF_FIG).
evidence: GH-R attenuated the caspase-1 cleavage and IL-1beta
